Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:09.880 --> 00:00:16.460
Today is Valentine's Day, one of the most popular and most celebrated holidays across the globe.

00:00:16.600 --> 00:00:20.540
And, as you all know, Valentine's Day is all about love.

00:00:20.540 --> 00:00:25.140
Unless, you're single, of course, then it's all about excruciating loneliness. But...

00:00:25.140 --> 00:00:26.760
What is love?

00:00:27.160 --> 00:00:28.720
Baby, don't hurt me.

00:00:28.880 --> 00:00:29.900
Don't hurt me.

00:00:30.020 --> 00:00:30.760
No more.

00:00:30.760 --> 00:00:39.380
Well, biologically speaking, love is a powerful neurological condition much like hunger or thirst, only more permanent.

00:00:39.460 --> 00:00:44.040
When you're truly in love, the brain can release a whole set of chemicals.

00:00:44.160 --> 00:00:49.960
Pheromones, dopamine, norepinephrine, serotonin, oxytocin, and vasopressin.

00:00:49.960 --> 00:00:55.100
What's interesting about this, though, is that love is more or less like a drug.

00:00:55.100 --> 00:00:59.900
Actually, when you're going through a breakup, it's exactly like a drug.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:09.260
Researchers have found that for heartbroken men and women, looking at photographs of their former loved ones activated regions in the brain associated with

00:01:09.260 --> 00:01:12.980
physical pain and intense cocaine addiction.

00:01:13.140 --> 00:01:21.560
In fact, the withdrawal symptoms can be so bad, that your body releases chemicals that significantly weakens your heart to the point where you could have

00:01:21.560 --> 00:01:29.000
a heart attack. You could actually die just by losing someone you love. It's something called broken heart syndrome.

00:01:29.040 --> 00:01:31.180
In other words, don't do love.

00:01:31.220 --> 00:01:33.020
Don't love and drive.

00:01:35.100 --> 00:01:39.740
Why do we use this shape to illustrate the heart and love?

00:01:39.740 --> 00:01:44.140
Actually, why do we use the heart as a representation of love at all?

00:01:44.260 --> 00:01:55.160
We're not exactly sure why. As far as historians can tell, the very first known depiction of a real heart as a symbol of love dates back to the middle of the 13th century.

00:01:55.240 --> 00:02:02.140
The use of the heart shape as a metaphor for the heart grew in popularity during the 15th and 16th centur[ies].

00:02:02.220 --> 00:02:06.520
For example, this symbol of Lutheranism was designed in 1530.

00:02:06.620 --> 00:02:12.140
And, this painting is from 1486 illustrating the crucifixion of Jesus Christ.

00:02:12.240 --> 00:02:19.240
Some believe that the heart shape was inspired by leaves. Or, it might have been one of the many heart-shaped flowers.

00:02:21.520 --> 00:02:27.360
If you're in a relationship right now, try looking [at] each other in the eye for three whole minutes.

00:02:27.360 --> 00:02:32.140
Also, make sure you have some type of heart rate monitor to observe both of your heart rates.

00:02:32.220 --> 00:02:39.640
Now, something strange should happen. If you're truly in love, your heart rates will begin to synchronize.

00:02:39.800 --> 00:02:44.360
As in, your hearts will start beating in almost exactly the same way.

00:02:44.660 --> 00:02:48.760
How or why this is happening, we simply don't know.

00:02:50.820 --> 00:02:58.300
The longest married couple in the world married in 1925 and are still married to this day.

00:02:58.340 --> 00:03:02.440
As of 2015, they have been married for 90 years.

00:03:04.760 --> 00:03:11.060
If you've ever been in love, you might have felt that it's almost difficult to concentrate on other things.

00:03:11.080 --> 00:03:18.080
Your mind is so filled with thoughts of this new love interest, you can't stop thinking about them. It's almost obsessive.

00:03:18.240 --> 00:03:25.880
Well, this isn't so strange, as your brain will have very similar activity to a person with obsessive compulsive disorder (OCD).

00:03:25.900 --> 00:03:33.060
It has actually been proven that in the early stages of a new romantic relationship, people have reduced cognitive control.

00:03:33.180 --> 00:03:39.420
In other words, you're so consumed by thoughts and feelings of this new person, that you become stupid.

00:03:41.300 --> 00:03:48.160
There's practically a phobia for everything, and yes, believe it or not, love is no exception.

00:03:48.280 --> 00:03:52.740
