00:04:32.880 --> 00:04:38.900
If you have a slight headache, it might be worth to just cuddle with your significant other for a while.

00:04:39.040 --> 00:04:47.400
The reason being that when you cuddle or when you're simply embraced in any way by someone you love, the hormone oxytocin is released and acts as a sort of

00:04:47.400 --> 00:04:53.600
natural painkiller. Even just looking at a picture of a loved one can be enough to relieve the pain.

00:04:55.680 --> 00:05:07.520
Love is complicated. You can love your family just as you can love a good meal, a pet, a friend, a hobby, and, of course, a significant other, like on Valentine's Day.

00:05:07.600 --> 00:05:17.980
This diversity of uses and meanings combine with the complexity of the feelings involved makes love unusually difficult to consistently define compared to other

00:05:17.980 --> 00:05:19.500
emotional states.

00:05:19.500 --> 00:05:23.720
Ancient Greeks identified love in a much more organized fashion.

00:05:23.720 --> 00:05:28.420
They actually used different words to describe different forms of love.

00:05:28.540 --> 00:05:36.880
For example, “love for your family”, “love between friends”, “romantic love”, and “divine or unconditional love”.

00:05:39.340 --> 00:05:47.860
The very first step to finding true romantic love is attraction. You need to be attracted to the person before you can love them.

00:05:47.920 --> 00:05:56.000
And, while attractiveness is, of course, relative to the situation and the individual in question, there's a few common patters on how most of us assess

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:00.960
attractiveness and who we ultimately choose to establish a romantic relationship with.

00:06:01.160 --> 00:06:04.940
One key point that researchers have found is symmetry.

00:06:04.940 --> 00:06:10.800
The more symmetrical your body is, specifically your face, the more attractive you are.

00:06:10.800 --> 00:06:17.320
The general idea is that good symmetry shows that an individual is healthy and will produce healthy offspring.

00:06:17.320 --> 00:06:23.980
And, while the face prove[s] to be a lot more important than the body, some big factors were hips and shoulders.

00:06:24.040 --> 00:06:33.700
Women with a waist significantly slimmer than the hips are the most desirable to men. And while the same (to a lesser extent) is true for men, it's more important to have

00:06:33.700 --> 00:06:41.060
broad shoulders. Another interesting thing is that love and attractiveness activate completely different regions of the brain.

00:06:41.120 --> 00:06:49.780
Feelings of romantic love activate regions on the right side of the brain, while looking at someone you find attractive activates the left side.

00:06:49.860 --> 00:06:55.700
But, most important of all, you should not be too much alike or too different.

00:06:55.700 --> 00:07:02.100
And, it seems to apply to all levels: genetics, behavior, appearance, and even what you smell like.

00:07:02.140 --> 00:07:10.640
The idea is that couples who have found a balance between not being identical and not too different are able to learn from each other while also having enough

00:07:10.640 --> 00:07:18.560
similarities to relate to one another. In other words, scientists have found that love is just as complicated as we think it is.

